description: Starting June 1, 2024, tobacco products in India will feature more disturbing images, including the face of a person with end-stage oral cancer and the warning "Tobacco causes painful death."  The change aims to combat the high tobacco usage rate, responsible for an estimated 1.3 million deaths annually.  The new warnings also include the national tobacco quit line number.
title: From next year, tobacco warnings to get grimmer

description: India's central government has drafted legislation to combat predatory lending practices by unregulated entities, including digital platforms. The proposed law introduces penalties of up to seven years imprisonment for illegal lenders and up to 10 years for those engaging in harassment and unlawful recovery tactics.
title: Government plans law to ban unregulated lending

description: A Navy speedboat collision with a ferry near Mumbai's Gateway of India tragically claimed 14 lives, with one person still missing. The overloaded ferry was en route to Elephanta Island. The speedboat, recently undergoing engine replacement, was being tested. Investigations are underway, focusing on the cause of the crash and the speedboat's operator.
title: Mumbai ferry toll hits 14, boatmen question Navy trial in busy area

description: In Varanasi, the Shri Kashi Vidwat Parishad (SKVP) is investigating a decades-closed temple in Madanpura, believed to be the Siddheshwar Mahadev temple. Scholars are meticulously researching ancient scriptures and maps to locate a water body and other temples mentioned in the texts, possibly buried under modern structures.
title: Kashi scholars say ‘lost & found’ shrine is of Shiva

description: The Reserve Bank of India expressed concerns over states' rising spending on subsidies like farm loan waivers and freebies, impacting funds for infrastructure and development.  State subsidies have surged, with revenue expenditure exceeding capital outlay in several states. While overall fiscal consolidation efforts are positive, RBI emphasizes the need for prioritizing capital expenditure for long-term growth.
title: Flagging farm loan waivers, cash transfers, other sops, RBI says rationalise subsidies

description: A ferry collided with a navy speedboat near Gateway of India. Passengers recalled the terrifying experience. Many struggled to find life jackets amid the chaos. Some passengers helped others.  The ferry driver allowed people on the roof for extra money.  Survivors criticized the lack of emergency preparedness on the ferry.
title: ‘Boat crew gave no safety instruction’: Survivor recounts Mumbai ferry accident

description: Rajya Sabha Deputy Chairman Harivansh rejected the INDIA bloc's notice for Vice-President Jagdeep Dhankhar's removal, citing insufficient notice period and alleging a deliberate attempt to tarnish the VP's reputation. Harivansh deemed the opposition's move a "misadventure" aimed at damaging constitutional institutions.
title: 'Flawed, bid to mar image': Vice President's removal notice junked

description: Rajya Sabha MP Phangnon Konyak accused Rahul Gandhi of misbehavior.  Konyak stated Gandhi's proximity made her uncomfortable.  She lodged a complaint with Rajya Sabha Chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar.  Congress MP Hibi Eden refuted the claims.  Eden said he witnessed the event. He confirmed Gandhi did not approach Konyak.
title: Parl scuffle: Naga MP alleges Rahul made her uncomfortable; blatant lie, says Cong
SGPC bars Damdama Sahib jathedar from doing duties

description: Union Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan criticized Congress for its alleged historical disregard for B.R. Ambedkar, citing a 2012 NCERT textbook cartoon depicting Jawaharlal Nehru "whipping" Ambedkar.  Pradhan suggested the cartoon reflected Congress's deep-seated contempt for Ambedkar, despite their recent public displays of respect.
title: Dharmendra Pradhan cites UPA-era NCERT textbook toon to target Congress

description: A pro-Khalistan group claimed responsibility for the fifth grenade attack on a Punjab police post in under a month.  The group cited alleged offensive remarks by police as motivation.  The attack caused minimal damage, and an autorickshaw believed to be involved was seized.  This follows a similar incident at Amritsar's Islamabad police station, raising concerns about deteriorating law and order.
title: Grenade blast at abandoned police post in Punjab, 5th such attack in a month

description: NITI Aayog proposes classifying factory worker housing as a separate category to streamline taxes and boost manufacturing.  This aims to address housing challenges hindering industrial growth and attract investment.  The report suggests zoning changes, affordable utilities, and GST exemptions for eligible units, crucial for achieving India's economic goals and supporting the projected influx of manufacturing jobs.
title: Niti Aayog calls for policy change to house workers near workplace

description: Home Minister Amit Shah convened a high-level security review in Jammu and Kashmir, emphasizing the government's commitment to eliminating terrorism. He lauded the collaborative efforts of security forces, resulting in decreased terrorist incidents and recruitment. Shah directed continued synchronized efforts, employing all available resources to achieve a terror-free J&K.
title: Home minister Amit Shah chairs J&K security review, calls for synergy

description: India's Ministry of Home Affairs has reinstated Protected Area Permits for Manipur, Nagaland, and Mizoram due to security concerns over influx from neighboring countries. This reverses a 2010 decision easing travel restrictions to boost tourism. Foreigners, excluding those from China, Pakistan, and Afghanistan, will now need permits.
title: Centre restricts entry of foreigners to Manipur, Mizoram & Nagaland

description: Luigi Mangione Thursday waived extradition in Pennsylvania and came to New York where he was charged with murder. But to the surprise of Mangione's lawyers, the federal authorities unsealed new charges against him which now make him eligible for the death penalty. There's no death penalty in New York law but Luigi Mangione become the rare case as he has been charged with federal murder.
title: Luigi Mangione becomes eligible for death penalty as he's charged with federal murder

description: The Indian rupee fell to a record low against the US dollar, crossing the 85 mark for the first time. This drop was influenced by the US Federal Reserve's indication of fewer-than-expected future rate cuts. While the decline makes imports costlier and benefits NRI remittances, its impact on export competitiveness is debated.
title: Rupee breaches 85/$ for 1st time on Fed's comment of fewer rate cuts in future
Parliament scuffle: Condition of BJP's Sarangi, Rajput stable, say doctors

description: Bangladesh's chief adviser, Muhammad Yunus, urged Pakistani PM Shehbaz Sharif to resolve outstanding issues from 1971 to improve bilateral relations.  While Sharif highlighted the 1974 tripartite agreement, Yunus emphasized the importance of a SAARC summit. Both leaders agreed to strengthen ties through trade, cultural exchanges, and cooperation in areas like sugar industry and dengue management.
title: 'Settle issues': What Yunus told Shehbaz Sharif on 1971 liberation war

description: A dispute has arisen between two villages in Karnataka over a temple buffalo, prompting police to conduct a DNA test. Kunibelakere villagers claim the buffalo, dedicated to their deity eight years ago, was stolen. Kulagatte villagers insist the animal is theirs, missing for two months.
title: Who owns the 'holy' buffalo? Karnataka cops rely on DNA test to settle fight

description: A Coimbatore resident paid ₹80,000 in ₹1 and ₹2 coins towards interim alimony ordered by the additional family court. The court directed him to pay the amount in notes. He complied the next day and was further directed to pay the remaining ₹1.2 lakh soon.
title: Man brings Rs 80,000 in coins to court to pay as interim alimony in TN

description: India's midday meal program, benefiting millions of schoolchildren, relies on the significantly underpaid labor of over 2.5 million cooks, predominantly women. They receive a mere fraction of the national minimum wage, effectively subsidizing the program by approximately ₹7,400 crore. This substantial savings for the central government exceeds half its allocated budget for the scheme.
title: Underpaid cooks subsidise midday meals by Rs 7,400 crore per year

description: The Supreme Court ruled against legitimizing unauthorized constructions, even with prolonged occupancy.  Demolition is mandated for structures violating laws, regardless of time or investment.  The court criticized states' regularization practices, citing environmental damage, and directed them to prioritize orderly urban development.  Further, it instructed financial institutions to verify occupancy certificates before loan sanctions.
title: Can’t legitimise illegal buildings, raze them: SC

description: Farmer leader Jagjit Singh Dallewal's health has deteriorated critically on the 24th day of his fast-unto-death, demanding guaranteed minimum support prices (MSP) for crops. He fainted and faces risks of cardiac arrest and organ failure due to severe electrolyte imbalance. The Supreme Court directed Punjab's government to ensure Dallewal undergoes a health check.
title: ‘Life hanging by a thread’: Docs on farmer leader's health as fast enters Day 24

description: Kansas City Chiefs quarterback Patrick Mahomes gifted his offensive line lavish Christmas presents, including Rolex watches, Oakley sunglasses, Lucchese boots, and Yeti coolers.  This generous gesture, costing a reported $100,000, highlights Mahomes' appreciation for his teammates and commitment to the Chiefs. Fans praised Mahomes' thoughtfulness, particularly the unique Rolex Sky Dweller watches.
title: Mahomes' $100K Christmas: Rolexes, Louis Vuitton, and lavish gifts for chiefs O-line

description: Mohammad Shami will miss Bengal's first Vijay Hazare Trophy game against Delhi.  He is recovering from knee swelling. Shami recently played in the Ranji and Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophies.  Indian captain Rohit Sharma wants Shami fully fit.  His availability for the Champions Trophy is uncertain.  Seamer Mukesh Kumar is in the Bengal squad.
title: Shami to be rested for Bengal's Vijay Hazare opener

description: The India-Australia Test series hangs in the balance at 1-1, with the final two matches crucial for World Test Championship Final qualification. A 2-2 series draw requires either a Sri Lankan upset over Australia or a Pakistani whitewash of South Africa for India to advance. A 1-1 finish necessitates a 2-0 Pakistan victory or a Sri Lankan win/draw against Australia.
title: Do India qualify for WTC Final if BGT ends in draw?

description: Ukrainian President Zelenskyy condemned Putin's suggestion of a "missile duel" with the US as irrational.  Putin proposed testing Russia's Oreshnik hypersonic missile against US defenses, claiming its superiority.  Russia first deployed the Oreshnik on November 21 against Dnipro, Ukraine, allegedly in retaliation for Ukrainian strikes on Russian territory.
title: 'Insane': Ukraine's Zelenskyy slams Putin's 'missile duel' suggestion with US

description: Elon Musk's five-word post on X urging against a spending bill triggered a political firestorm, fracturing Republican support and pushing the US closer to a government shutdown.  His social media blitz, echoing Trump's call for legislative delay, highlights the billionaire's unprecedented unelected influence, raising concerns about democratic norms and federal stability.
title: Meet the man who could shut US govt with a five-word post on X

description: Tensions flared outside Parliament as NDA and INDIA bloc MPs clashed, accusing each other of disrespecting B.R. Ambedkar. Two BJP MPs were injured in the scuffle, leading to an FIR against Rahul Gandhi for alleged assault. The BJP claims Gandhi pushed senior members, while Congress alleges BJP MPs threatened and shoved Mallikarjun Kharge.
title: Lok Sabha Speaker bars protests at Parliament gates: Report

description: A Mumbai ferry accident claimed 14 lives after a collision with a Navy vessel.  Rescuers continue searching for a missing seven-year-old boy.  98 passengers survived, some with injuries. A Navy inquiry board is investigating the cause, and charges have been filed against the naval speed boat operator.
title: Mumbai ferry accident: Missing body recovered, death toll rises to 14

description: The Indian Air Force confirmed human error as the cause of the helicopter crash that killed Chief of Defence Staff General Bipin Rawat, his wife, and 11 others. Data reveals 34 aircraft accidents during the recent defence plan, with human error responsible for half.
title: Human error behind chopper crash that killed CDS Bipin Rawat: Report

description: Delhi police filed an FIR against Congress leader Rahul Gandhi following a BJP complaint alleging physical assault and incitement during a Parliament scuffle.  The confrontation stemmed from alleged insults to B.R. Ambedkar, injuring two BJP MPs.  Congress denied the accusations, claiming BJP MPs manhandled Gandhi and Kharge.  A counter-complaint was also filed by Congress.
title: Police file FIR against Rahul over 'assault' on BJP MPs: What has he been charged with?

description: The Milwaukee Bucks secured the 2024 NBA Cup title, defeating the Oklahoma City Thunder. Assistant coach Darvin Ham reflected on his challenging 2022 season with the Los Angeles Lakers, citing LeBron James's age and Anthony Davis's injuries as contributing factors to lineup difficulties.
title: Bucks coach Darvin blames LeBron's age, Davis’ injury for Lakers’ lineup choices

description: Karnataka BJP MLC CT Ravi was detained after state minister Laxmi Hebbalkar filed an FIR alleging derogatory language against her.  Ravi denies the accusations, calling them false and demanding video verification.  Congress leaders condemned Ravi's alleged remarks, while supporters of Hebbalkar protested the incident.
title: Derogatory remarks: K'taka BJP leader booked, taken into custody

description: The 2025 ICC Champions Trophy will follow a hybrid model. Pakistan will host the tournament. Matches involving India will occur at a neutral venue. Mohammad Amir welcomed the decision. He emphasized the importance of the India-Pakistan clash. The ICC also announced hybrid models for other tournaments. These include the 2025 Women's World Cup and the 2026 Men's T20 World Cup.
title: 'Even if IND vs PAK happens on moon ... ': Amir on hybrid model
Rahul's switch from white to blue t-shirt and the Ambedkar connection
From protests to FIRs: How Ambedkar row took a shock turn

description: The Los Angeles Lakers are exploring trade options to bolster their roster around LeBron James.  General Manager Rob Pelinka is reportedly considering familiar faces like Kyle Kuzma and Brandon Ingram, as well as other players like Walker Kessler and Cam Johnson.  The Lakers' aim is to improve their playoff chances after a middling start to the season.
title: Lakers Trade Rumor: GM Pelinka eyes two ex-Lakers to bolster LeBron's postseason.

description: Elon Musk and SpaceX are under investigation by three US military branches for allegedly violating reporting protocols regarding meetings with foreign officials, including Vladimir Putin.  The Air Force denied Musk a higher security clearance due to these concerns, prompted by senators' alarm over Musk's reported conversations with Putin and other Russian officials.
title: 'Elon is Russian agent' claims worry US Air Force chief

description: The ICC adopted a hybrid model for its 2024-2027 tournaments, addressing India's refusal to play in Pakistan due to security concerns.  Matches between India and Pakistan will occur at neutral venues, allowing both nations to participate. This model, similar to the 2023 Asia Cup, ensures tournament integrity while navigating political tensions.
title: What is hybrid model? Formula for India, Pakistan ICC matches

description: Ravichandran Ashwin, 38, announced his shocking retirement from international cricket after the third India vs Australia Test. His father attributed the decision to 'humiliation' Ashwin faced due to repeated omissions from the playing XI.  Ashwin later clarified on social media, requesting understanding for his father's untrained remarks.
title: 'Leave him alone': Ashwin on father's 'humiliation' remark

description: Maharashtra Chief Minister Davendra Fadnavis claimed terror funds were used in the state elections.  He cited a Malegaon case with suspicious transactions of Rs 1000 crore.  Fadnavis alleged foreign interference and a Nepal meeting discussing replacing EVMs.  The meeting involved organizations associated with the Bharat Jodo Yatra.  These organizations campaigned for the opposition.  The ATS is investigating the matter.
title: 'Foreign interference': CM Fadnavis makes big claim on Maha polls

description: Canada plans to overhaul its Express Entry immigration system by eliminating points for job offers backed by a Labour Market Impact Assessment (LMIA) to combat fraud. This change could significantly impact Indian applicants, who constitute a large portion of successful candidates.
title: Indians eyeing permanent residency in Canada may soon face big roadblock
'India said it best': Putin talks about Brics, ties with PM Modi in annual presser

description: Roman Reigns, following his Survivor Series triumph, remains a captivating enigma.  Paul Heyman's cryptic remarks about a private jet meeting with Reigns have ignited speculation about the Bloodline's future.  With Reigns set to face Solo Sikoa in a Tribal Combat match, tensions are high.  This upcoming SmackDown clash could either solidify the faction or shatter it, reshaping the WWE landscape.
title: WWE SmackDown countdown: Heyman receives 'mysterious' call from Reigns

description: Before settling down with Becky Lynch, WWE superstar Seth Rollins experienced a series of public romances. His early relationship with Leighla Schultz, a hairstylist and wrestler, ended after a broken engagement. A subsequent relationship with Zahra Schreiber, a fellow NXT wrestler, was marred by leaked photos and her WWE release.
title: Seth Rollins dating history: Exploring past relationships of the visionary

description: Anushka Sharma and Virat Kohli are one of the most celebrated couples in Bollywood, and the duo never fails to grab headlines when it comes to their dreamy family life, including their children, Vamika and Akaay. Earlier this year, rumours began circulating that the family might make a permanent move to London. These rumours were given further credibility when his childhood coach addressed the matter and shared information about Virat’s decision to move to London with Anushka and the children.
title: Anushka Sharma & Virat Kohli to settle in London permanently

description: Binance CEO Changpeng Zhao called out 5ireChain.  5ireChain used Zhao's selfie for promotion.  The selfie was taken at an event.  Zhao clarified no collaboration exists.  He said selfies are for personal use. Zhao stated explicit permission is needed for promotional use.
title: Angry Binance CEO to Indian CEO: This is exactly how NOT to use selfie

description: Amazon India is revising its Prime Video usage terms. From January, 2025, a single Prime membership will allow streaming on up to five devices, but only two of those can be TVs. This change means households streaming Prime Video on more than two televisions will need a separate subscription for each additional TV.
title: Amazon Prime membership rules are changing starting January 2025

description: Prime Minister Modi and King Charles III discussed shared interests like the Commonwealth, climate action, and sustainability, reaffirming their commitment to a stronger partnership between India and the UK.  The conversation follows reports of the King and Queen's planned visit to India, marking the King's first official trip since his ascension.
title: PM Modi speaks with King Charles III, discusses climate action

description: Angry passengers vandalized the Antyodaya Express at Basti station.  They broke a window and grill to enter the locked train.  The train was overcrowded.  Passengers inside had locked the doors to prevent more boarding.  RPF is investigating the incident.  They are using video footage to identify the vandals. No arrests have been made yet.
title: Watch: Incensed over locked doors, passengers vandalise Antyodaya Express

description: Ravichandran, father of Indian just-retired Ashwin, revealed that his son's sudden retirement stemmed from alleged humiliation within the team. The family was shocked by the decision, believing Ashwin's career had more to offer. Repeated omissions from the playing XI likely fueled Ashwin's retirement, a move his father suggested was emotionally difficult but perhaps inevitable given the circumstances.
title: Ashwin quit because of 'humiliation', claims father

description: Union Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan criticized Congress for their sudden reverence for B.R. Ambedkar, calling it "crocodile tears." He highlighted a 2012 NCERT cartoon depicting Nehru whipping Ambedkar, suggesting Congress's historical disrespect. Pradhan contrasted this with PM Modi's honoring of Ambedkar, accusing Congress of harboring hatred towards him from Nehru to Rahul Gandhi.
title: 'Cong has always hated Ambedkar': Edu minister shares 'shameful' cartoon

description: Maharashtra chief minister Devendra Fadnavis assured NCP leader Ajit Pawar of a future chief ministership.  Fadnavis outlined a three-shift work schedule, with Pawar handling mornings, himself working from noon to midnight, and Deputy CM Shinde covering the night shift.  Pawar, known for his CM ambitions, recently rejoined the government after splitting the NCP.
title: 'You will be CM one day': Devendra Fadnavis tells Ajit Pawar

description: The Syrian conflict echoes the US withdrawal from Afghanistan in 2021.  Rebel groups seized Russian weapons. This mirrors the Taliban's acquisition of US equipment.  Both situations highlight the risks of abandoned weaponry. Russia's losses include advanced systems.  These losses affect Russia's military strength. The Syrian conflict destabilizes the Middle East.
title: Syria vs Afghanistan: Whose weapon losses hurt more—Russia or US?

description: The New York Knicks and Minnesota Timberwolves are set to clash at the Target Center on December 19, 2024, at 9:30 PM ET. Both teams are coming off recent wins, setting the stage for a competitive matchup. The Knicks boast a deeper roster, while the Timberwolves rely on the star power of Edwards and Gobert.
title: New York Knicks vs Minnesota Timberwolves (12/19): All you need to know

description: Delhi is facing a wave of bomb threats targeting schools, hospitals, and transportation hubs since May. Over 50 incidents have been reported, but investigations are stalled due to the perpetrators' use of VPNs and proxy servers to mask their location.
title: Delhi Police calls these proxy servers problem in solving bomb threats

description: Dropbox CEO Drew Houston introduced a new meeting style. It involves reading memos before discussions. This method is inspired by Amazon's founder Jeff Bezos. It replaces presentations with written documents. Participants read for 10-20 minutes before discussing. This allows for deeper understanding and better collaboration. Dropbox uses Dropbox Paper for comments and feedback.
title: Dropbox CEO is 'fan' of Amazon founder’s 'Memo-First' meeting culture

description: Jammu and Kashmir chief minister Omar Abdullah met with Union Home Minister Amit Shah to discuss the restoration of statehood for the region.  Abdullah sought a timeline for the process and clarification on the government's authority under the current Union Territory status.  He expressed optimism about the restoration and highlighted the need to address various issues with the Home Minister.
title: Omar Abdullah meets Amit Shah, discusses early statehood restoration

description: The Anti-Corruption Bureau (ACB) filed a case against former minister KT Rama Rao, ex-principal secretary Aravind Kumar, and HMDA chief engineer BLN Reddy for alleged financial irregularities. They are accused of diverting Rs. 55 crores to a London-based company during the Formula E racing event in Hyderabad.
title: KTR booked as prime accused in Formula E case in Telangana

description: BJP and Congress MPs clashed outside Parliament, leading to accusations of assault from both sides.  BJP's Pratap Sarangi alleged Rahul Gandhi pushed an MP, while Congress President Kharge claimed BJP MPs injured his knee.  Both parties filed police complaints, with BJP accusing Gandhi of assault and Congress alleging misbehavior against Kharge.
title: FIR vs FIR: Cong, BJP lodge complaints against each other over scuffle

description: Rahul Gandhi denied BJP's accusations of shoving their MPs, claiming it's a tactic to divert attention from Amit Shah's remarks on Ambedkar and the Adani issue.  Gandhi and Kharge demanded Shah's apology and resignation. The BJP accused Gandhi of "goondaism" and deliberately scuffling with their MPs, escalating the political clash.
title: Sansad scuffle: Rahul alleges 'distraction' ploy; BJP calls it 'goondaism'

description: Ravichandran Ashwin retired from cricket after the drawn third Test against Australia.  Kapil Dev felt Ashwin's farewell was inadequate.  Ashwin took 537 Test wickets and 765 international wickets. He played 106 Tests, 116 ODIs, and 65 T20Is.  He was part of India's 2011 World Cup and 2013 Champions Trophy wins.  Ashwin announced his retirement alongside Rohit Sharma in the post-match press conference.
title: Kapil Dev on Ashwin's retirement: I wouldn't have...

description: Spin-bowling all-rounder Ravichandran Ashwin's sudden retirement from international cricket in the middle of the Test series in Australia has sparked debate. Former Pakistan player Basit Ali believes if Virat Kohli was India captain, he would have persuaded Ashwin to delay the announcement until after the Border Gavaskar Trophy, citing India needing his services in the Sydney Test.
title: 'If Virat was India captain, he wouldn't have let Ashwin retire'

description: Putin declared Russia's readiness for a "missile duel" with the US, showcasing the Oreshnik hypersonic missile. He confirmed plans to meet Assad and expressed willingness to engage with Trump.  Putin also addressed Russia's economic overheating, supporting the central bank's measures to curb inflation and projecting slower growth in 2025.
title: Russia set for a missile duel with US, says president Vladimir Putin

description: India will play its matches in next year’s Champions Trophy at a neutral venue, having refused to travel to host nation and arch-rival Pakistan, the International Cricket Council announced on Thursday after weeks of deliberations. In return, Pakistan will play its matches in future ICC tournaments hosted by India at neutral venues. The agreement also covers the ICC Women’s Cricket World Cup 2025, hosted by India, and the ICC Men’s T20 World Cup 2026, co-hosted by India and Sri Lanka, the ICC statement confirmed.
title: ICC Champions Trophy will be held in hybrid model across Pak, neutral venue

description: Virat Kohli clashed with the media at Melbourne Airport, believing his children were being filmed. He expressed his need for privacy, especially around his family. The misunderstanding was cleared up, with Kohli shaking hands with the cameraperson before leaving for the team hotel. Kohli and the Indian team will next be involved in the Boxing Day Test.
title: Watch video: Virat Kohli gets angry on arrival in Melbourne

description: BJP MP Phangnon Konyak has accused Congress leader Rahul Gandhi of misbehaving with her during a Parliament protest. Konyak alleges Gandhi's close proximity and loud voice made her uncomfortable. This follows another incident where a BJP MP accused Gandhi of pushing him. Gandhi denies the allegations, claiming BJP MPs obstructed him.
title: 'Dignity deeply hurt by Rahul': BJP woman MP writes to RS chairman

description: The US government backs India's extradition request for Tahawwur Rana, a suspect in the 2008 Mumbai attacks. Rana, fighting extradition, petitioned the Supreme Court, but the US Solicitor General urged the court to deny his plea.
title: 26/11 accused to be extradited to India? US asks SC to dismiss plea

description: Rajya Sabha Deputy Chairman Harivansh rejected an impeachment notice against Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar filed by 60 opposition members. The notice, alleging bias, was deemed flawed, hasty, and designed to damage Dhankhar's reputation. Harivansh criticized the opposition's attempt to undermine constitutional institutions and personally target the Vice President with unfounded claims.
title: No-trust move against VP Dhankhar dismissed: Report

description: On the other hand, Social media platforms have been flooded with posts expressing disapproval of the Academy’s decision. Director Hansal Mehta, posting a screenshot of the final nominees wrote, " Film Federation of India does it again! Their strike rate and selection of films year after year is impeccable."
title: Laapataa Ladies bows out of Oscar race: Where are we going wrong?

description: Sukumar's "Pushpa 2: The Rule" nears ₹975 crore globally in two weeks, surpassing "Stree 2" and "Jawan" in Hindi collections with ₹607.35 crore.  Telugu collections reached ₹323.3 crore.  The film's success continues overseas, earning ₹114 crore in North America. "Pushpa 3: The Rampage" is confirmed.
title: Pushpa 2 box office collection day 14

description: A Goa homestay owner posted a video of a messy guest room. The video went viral. It showed unwashed dishes and a cluttered space.  The owner expressed disappointment.  Some viewers supported the owner. Others defended the guests.  They cited the cleaning fee as justification. The incident triggered a discussion about respect and responsibility in rented accommodations.
title: Goa homestay owner's 'house destroyed' post divides internet

description: India's tax department has clarified reporting rules for foreign income and assets. Non-disclosure invites hefty penalties under the Black Money Act, including a potential Rs 10 lakh fine and legal action.
title: Avoid Rs 10 lakh income tax penalty! Complete this in ITR by Dec 31

description: A French court is set to deliver verdicts in a mass rape trial involving 51 men, including Dominique Pelicot, accused of drugging and raping his wife, Gisèle, over nine years. Pelicot used an online website to invite men to his home to assault his unconscious wife. He also filmed his daughters-in-law and is suspected in other cold cases.
title: Who is Dominique Pelicot? Accused in mass rape trial in France

description: Following a fatal ferry-Navy vessel collision near Mumbai that claimed 13 lives, life jackets are now mandatory for all passengers on boat rides from the Gateway of India. While some welcomed the move, others stressed the need for instructions on proper usage. Survivors reported insufficient life jackets on the ill-fated ferry.
title: Boat accident: Life jackets now mandatory for ferry rides from Gateway of India

description: India's spin-bowling legend Ravichandran Ashwin received a heartwarming welcome from his daughter and family upon returning to Chennai after announcing his retirement from international cricket a day earlier in Australia. Ashwin, India's second-highest Test wicket-taker, shared his daughter's touching message of support on social media after his arrival back home.
title: Ashwin's daughter has a sweet farewell message for her dad

description: Ashneer Grover and Anupam Mittal's feud continues, with Ashneer recently joking about Anupam's reluctance to invest. He humorously recounted his struggles to secure funding from Anupam, highlighting Anupam's tendency to offer advice rather than money. Anupam, in turn, made a cryptic remark about the 'demise' of some season one sharks.
title: Ashneer Grover on strangest thing he did to promote his brand: I went to...
Gisèle Pelicot's ex-husband Dominique found guilty of all charges
Who is Pratap Sarangi? BJP MP injured after alleged 'push' from Rahul Gandhi

description: Apple and Meta are clashing over data privacy under new EU digital rules. Apple accuses Meta of seeking excessive access to its systems, potentially jeopardizing user data. Meta has made numerous requests to integrate with Apple's software, more than any other company. Apple argues granting these requests could allow Meta to monitor user activity extensively.
title: Wants access to phone calls, photos...: Apple's warning to iPhone users

description: Chaos erupted outside Parliament as BJP MP Pratap Sarangi accused Rahul Gandhi of pushing him, causing an injury. Gandhi denied the claim, alleging BJP MPs obstructed and threatened him. Congress shared a video appearing to show BJP MPs blocking their entry to Parliament.
title: BJP MPs pushed, threatened me: Rahul after scuffle in Parliament complex

description: Virat Kohli reportedly clashed with media at Melbourne Airport upon arrival for the Boxing Day Test, seemingly upset by cameras focused on his family. Kohli's recent form has been inconsistent despite a century in Perth, with other innings yielding minimal runs. The Border-Gavaskar series is tied 1-1 after a drawn third Test.
title: Virat Kohli gets upset with media on arrival in Melbourne

description: Opposition leader Mallikarjun Kharge reported being pushed by BJP MPs during a Parliament protest.  The incident caused him to fall and injure his knees.  Kharge struggled to enter the building.  The INDIA bloc protested, demanding an apology from home minister Amit Shah.  The protest escalated into a shouting match between opposing parties.
title: 'I limped to House': Kharge accuses BJP MPs of 'physical assault' in scuffle

description: A scuffle broke out outside Parliament between BJP and INDIA bloc MPs after Rahul Gandhi approached BJP MP Pratap Chandra Sarangi, who had been injured during the confrontation. BJP MPs accused Gandhi of pushing Sarangi, while Gandhi denied the allegations and claimed he was obstructed and pushed by BJP MPs.
title: 'Gundagardi karte ho?' What happened when Rahul approached injured BJP MP

description: Four children were injured, one critically, during a December 12 encounter between security forces and Maoists in Chhattisgarh, India.  Villagers allege they were harvesting crops when fired upon.  Maoists claim five of the seven killed were villagers, while police say Maoists used the children as human shields.  Tribal rights activists rescued the injured children and are demanding accountability.
title: Bullet stuck in neck: 4 Chhattisgarh kids ‘hurt in crossfire’

description: Jasprit Bumrah's exceptional performance with 21 wickets at an average of 10.90 in the Border Gavaskar Trophy has highlighted India's dependence on him.  Mohammed Shami's absence is felt, while Siraj provides support with 13 wickets. Brett Lee praises Bumrah's world-class bowling, noting his significant contribution to the Indian pace attack.
title: 'Unfortunately, India have no Mohammed Shami in Australia'

description: OpenAI has launched a new way to access ChatGPT via a dedicated phone number (1-800-CHATGPT) and WhatsApp.  US users get 15 free minutes monthly via the phone line. This experimental feature offers a simplified way to interact with the AI, even on basic phones.  While convenient, users needing advanced features should stick to traditional ChatGPT access.
title: ChatGPT is now available on WhatsApp, calls: How to access

description: Arvind Kejriwal criticizes Amit Shah's remarks on Dr. B.R. Ambedkar, labeling them disrespectful and indicative of the BJP's perspective on the architect of the Indian Constitution.  Kejriwal questions BJP allies, urging reflection on Shah's statement, which allegedly hurt millions. Shah's comments, made during a Rajya Sabha debate, targeted the Congress for invoking Ambedkar's name for political gain.
title: 'Those who love Ambedkar can't support BJP': Kejriwal's letter to Nitish, Naidu

description: A naval speedboat collided with a tourist ferry near Mumbai's Gateway of India, resulting in 13 deaths. The ferry sank after the collision, which occurred during a speedboat trial.  Rescue efforts were undertaken by nearby vessels. Security measures were increased, and tourist activities were suspended following the tragic incident.
title: How JNPT pilot boats became saviours during one of Mumbai harbour's deadliest crashes

description: Television actress Devoleena Bhattacharjee and her husband, Shanawaz Shaikh, joyfully welcomed a baby boy on December 18, 2024. The Bigg Boss 13 star shared the exciting news on Instagram, receiving a flood of congratulations from fellow celebrities and fans.
title: Devoleena Bhattacharjee and husband Shanawaz welcome a baby boy

description: Nasa's James Webb and Chandra observatories have unveiled a stunning image of star cluster NGC 602, resembling a cosmic wreath. Located 200,000 light-years away, the cluster's ring of dust and gas, illuminated by young, massive stars emitting X-rays, offers insights into the early universe due to its low heavy element content.
title: Nasa unveils image of wreath-like star cluster, symbolising cycle of life
Ambedkar row: BJP cites old Pitroda post on social media to counter oppn

description: Google warns Gmail users of increased holiday scams, highlighting a 35% reduction in reported scams due to enhanced security features.  They advise caution against phishing emails, fake shipping notifications, and charity scams. Gmail's spam filters, warning labels, and two-factor authentication offer protection, but users should remain vigilant, verify sender addresses, and avoid impulsive actions.
title: Google has a ‘Gmail scam warning’, wants you to not miss these simple tips

description: RJD chief Lalu Prasad Yadav demanded Home Minister Amit Shah's resignation, accusing him of "madness" and harboring hatred towards B.R. Ambedkar following Shah's parliamentary remarks about invoking Ambedkar's name. Opposition parties protested, demanding an apology, while Tejashwi Yadav labeled Shah's party "anti-constitution." PM Modi defended Shah, accusing Congress of distorting the remarks and having an "anti-Ambedkar history.
title: 'Gone mad, should resign': Lalu Yadav takes jibe on Amit Shah

description: Spanish police arrested two individuals in connection with the disappearance of a 33-year-old Cuban man in October 2023. A Google Street View image, showing a white-shrouded object being loaded into a car, aided the investigation. While not the sole factor, the image corroborated other evidence, including suspicious text messages sent from the victim's phone.
title: Google Maps spots ‘white object’ in car trunk, cracks Spain murder case

description: The Indian cricket team departed Brisbane for Melbourne, gearing up for the Boxing Day Test against Australia at the MCG. With the series tied 1-1, India aims to replicate their 2020 Boxing Day Test victory, where they triumphed by eight wickets under Ajinkya Rahane's captaincy.
title: Watch: Team India departs from Brisbane to Melbourne for Boxing Day Test

description: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella, after a decade-long quest to secure an Apple search deal, finds an unexpected win through OpenAI's recent partnership with Apple. Nadella expressed his excitement, revealing Microsoft's persistent, even audacious, attempts to replace Google on Apple devices.
title: 10-year-wait that made Microsoft CEO 'thrilled' about this 'Apple deal'

description: Ravichandran Ashwin returned to Chennai after retiring from international cricket midway through India's tour of Australia. He received a grand welcome from family, friends and neighbours. Ashwin played for 14 years and took 537 Test wickets. He made the retirement announcement after the third Test of the Border Gavaskar Trophy in Brisbane.
title: Ashwin back home after shock retirement in Australia - Watch

description: Sambhal MP Zia-ur-Rahman Barq is facing power theft charges after officials discovered discrepancies with his electricity meter. A 2KW domestic connection allegedly bypassed the meter, powering appliances like ACs, resulting in a detected load of 16,480 watts. While officials replaced the meter, Barq's lawyer denies any wrongdoing, citing a 5KW solar connection and a generator as the power source.
title: Samajwadi Party MP accused of power theft in Sambhal, FIR filed

description: A California man, Alexander Paffendorf, 20, has been detained for allegedly conspiring with 15-year-old Natalie Rupnow in the Wisconsin school shooting.  Paffendorf reportedly messaged Rupnow about his plans to attack a government building with explosives and firearms.  He is now under a restraining order, surrendering his weapons, while authorities investigate the connection between the two and the tragic school attack.
title: New twist in Wisconsin shooting: Who is Alexander Paffendorf?

description: Prakash Ambedkar, grandson of B.R. Ambedkar, criticized Home Minister Amit Shah's remarks on the Constitution's architect, calling them reflective of the BJP's historical opposition. The controversy stems from Shah's comment about invoking Ambedkar's name, sparking outrage and demands for an apology from opposition parties.
title: 'Nothing new': What BR Ambedkar's grandson said on Amit Shah's remarks

description: Veteran Malayalam actorMeena Ganesh, 81, passed away at a private hospital in Shoranur, Palakkad, following a cerebral stroke.  She had a prolific career spanning over a hundred films, numerous serials, and plays.  Starting with theatre at 19, she debuted in films with "Manimuzhakkam" and gained recognition for her role in "Mukhamudra."  She is survived by her son and daughter.
title: Veteran Malayalam actor Meena Ganesh passes away at 81

description: In a chilling turn of events at a Deoghar wedding, the groom fainted mid-ceremony due to the frigid temperatures.  The bride, interpreting this as a sign of potential health issues, abruptly called off the wedding, leaving the groom's family in shock and returning home alone.
title: Groom collapses due to cold wave, angry bride calls off marriage
California declares emergency to combat rising bird flu infection in dairy
Did Sam Altman’s OpenAI murder whistleblower Suchir Balaji?

description: Jasprit Bumrah, after overcoming back issues, became India's leading Test wicket-taker in Australia, surpassing Kapil Dev. His exceptional performance in the ongoing series, including a player-of-the-match award, has earned praise from cricket legends like Ricky Ponting and Travis Head, who consider him one of the greatest fast bowlers.
title: 'India's greatest fast bowler...': Aussies in awe of Jasprit Bumrah

description: Tragedy struck near Mumbai Harbour as a Navy speedboat collided with a passenger ferry, resulting in 13 deaths. The ferry, Neelkamal, capsized after the impact, leaving 101 rescued and several injured. A viral video captured the incident. Rescue operations involved multiple agencies. Survivors recounted the chaotic scene, with some still missing loved ones.
title: Video: The moment Navy speedboat rammed into Mumbai ferry

description: Ravichandran Ashwin's shock retirement from Test cricket reportedly stemmed from being benched during the Border-Gavaskar Trophy opener in Perth. Rohit Sharma convinced Ashwin to delay it and he was included in the eleven for the the pink-ball Test in Adelaide. But his subsequent exclusion from the match in Brisbane seemingly finalized his decision.
title: Did a broken promise lead to Ashwin's shock retirement?
'We both have been wronged': Mallya responds to Lalit Modi's birthday wish

description: Tragedy struck Mumbai's harbor as a naval speedboat collided with a tourist ferry near Gateway of India, claiming 13 lives, including a sailor and two company technicians. The ferry, Neelkamal, sank after the impact, prompting a rescue operation by nearby vessels. Survivors, including women and children, were rushed to hospitals.
title: Boat accident: 'Was recording video thinking speedboat was doing stunts, then it hit us’
'Zap it, put it in a bag and ... ': How US military responds to drone intrusions over bases

description: R Ashwin, India's second-highest Test wicket-taker, unexpectedly announced his retirement from international cricket.  Overlooked in favor of Ravindra Jadeja and Washington Sundar, Ashwin's career was marked by resilience and adaptation. From overcoming early rejections to mastering the carrom ball, his innovative approach made him a formidable force, especially in home conditions, forming a potent partnership with Jadeja.
title: How Ashwin thrived on reinvention throughout his career
Encounter breaks out between security forces and terrorists in J&K's Kulgam
Times Internet, ICICI Bank unveil super-premium metal credit card

description: Allu Arjun's "Pushpa 2" continues its box office rampage, nearing ₹1000 crore globally in just two weeks.  The film's Telugu and Hindi versions lead the charge, with strong contributions from other South Indian languages.  Despite weekday dips, "Pushpa 2" is expected to hit the ₹1000 crore mark soon. The film will be available on Netflix in February 2025.
title: Pushpa 2 heads towards the Rs1000 crore club
Who was Rubi Patricia? Wisconsin school shooting victim identified

description: Veteran Indian spinner Ravichandran Ashwin unexpectedly announced his retirement from international cricket amidst the Border-Gavaskar Trophy in Brisbane. Citing a desire to focus on club cricket, the 38-year-old all-rounder concluded his illustrious 14-year career, marked by over 500 Test wickets and six centuries.
title: Ashwin's off-break: Legend's spin cycle comes to an abrupt end

description: Microsoft President Brad Smith urged stronger action against state-sponsored cyberattacks, particularly from Russia, China, and Iran. He highlighted the increasing frequency of attacks and called for international cooperation on cybersecurity.  Smith also acknowledged Microsoft's own security challenges and emphasized the company's commitment to improvement.
title: Microsoft president makes this 'China and Russia' request to Donald Trump

description: Tech consultant Nima Momeni was found guilty of second-degree murder in the stabbing death of Cash App founder Bob Lee in San Francisco. Momeni faces 16 years to life, and his attorney plans to appeal. The April incident sparked debate about San Francisco's safety.
title: IT company owner convicted for murder of Cash App founder Bob Lee
Sebi tightens rules for SME IPOs, merchant banking biz
Alumni of IIT Delhi lead list of top startup founders
Wisconsin school shooter linked to site showing gruesome deaths

description: Sri Lankan spin legend Muttiah Muralitharan praised Ravichandran Ashwin's illustrious Test career after the Indian off-spinner announced his retirement. Muralitharan commended Ashwin's transition from batsman to bowler, highlighting his dedication and achievement of 537 Test wickets, placing him second in India's all-time rankings and seventh globally.  Muralitharan admired Ashwin's continuous learning and development of variations throughout his career.
title: 'Ashwin started as a batsman...': Muralitharan hails India spinner

description: Vijay Mallya asserts the banks have recovered twice the Kingfisher Airlines judgement debt.  The Finance Minister reported recoveries exceeding Rs 14,000 crore.  Mallya insists the debt was Rs 6,203 crore. He says he repaid the Rs 900 crore IDBI loan.  Mallya denies wrongdoing and seeks relief. The government continues pursuing economic offenders.
title: 'Entitled to relief': Mallya reacts to Nirmala's Rs 14,131 cr debt recovery remarks

description: Elon Musk, owner of X (formerly Twitter), has declared hashtags obsolete and visually unappealing. He urged users to discontinue their use, suggesting X's algorithms no longer require them for content discovery. This marks a significant shift from hashtags' traditional role in categorizing and surfacing trending topics since 2007. Musk's aversion to hashtags isn't new, having expressed his dislike last year.
title: Elon Musk to Twitter users: Stop using ..., they look ugly
